{"type":"message","id":"932fcd75","parentId":"ea063289","timestamp":"2026-03-03T16:22:38.413Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Initiating Note Retrieval**\n\nI'm focusing on retrieving the \"Grocery list\" note using the `memo` CLI. I'm leveraging its search function; earlier attempts with `memo notes -s \"Grocery` looked promising, but I'm refining the search query for precision. Next, I'll analyze the results.\n\n\n**Refining Search Parameters**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the correct syntax for the `memo` CLI search. Previously, I incorrectly used `-s` expecting it to work like a positional argument. The tool expects the search term as an argument to `--search`. So, `memo notes --search \"Grocery list\"` should be the correct command. I will use it to attempt retrieving the note. After that, I will attempt to analyze the output.\n\n\n**Confirming Search Query Syntax**\n\nI've tested `memo notes --search \"Grocery list\"` as the query and am now confident in the correct syntax for note retrieval. The previous attempts were stymied by incorrect argument passing. I'm moving toward executing the command and assessing the result, focusing on how the note content is returned. If it's directly in the output, I'll proceed directly to summarization. Otherwise, I will need to consider whether an additional command will be needed to get the notes.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1772554958402_12","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"memo notes --search \"Grocery list\"","pty":true},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-2.5-flash-lite","usage":{"input":32671,"output":357,"cacheRead":32098,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33028,"cost":{"input":0.0032671,"output":0.0001428,"cacheRead":0.00080245,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00421235}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772554954625}}
